The synonymy of the taxon monedulaeformis Rambur with Bembecia uroceriformis (Treitschke 1834) is already stated by Rambur (1858[-1866]), confirmed by pl. 2, fig. 2. The taxon has erroneously been assigned to Synanthedon andrenaeformis (Laspeyres 1801) since Boisduval (1840) and Staudinger (1856). Dalla Torre & Strand (1925) linked it with Chamaesphecia anthraciformis (Rambur 1832) because of the homonymy with S. anthraciformis Esper (a synonym of S. andrenaeformis).
